src/lexicographical/colexicographical.js
colexicographical
description:
Generates a binary colexicographical comparator
from a binary comparator.

https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lexicographical_order#Colexicographic_order

compare( a, b ) should always return
  - a negative value if a < b
  - a positive value if a > b
  - zero if a === b

compare should express an increasing ordering

name: src/native/decreasing.js
content:
/**
 * Compare two objects in decreasing order using the native comparison and
 * equality operators.
 *
 * @param {Object} a - The first parameter.
 * @param {Object} b - The second parameter.
 * @return {Number} -1 if a > b, 0 if a === b, and 1 otherwise.
 */
export const decreasing = ( a , b ) => ( a > b ) ? -1 : ( a === b ) ? 0 : 1 ;

name: decreasing
description:
Compare two objects in decreasing order using the native comparison and
equality operators.

return.description: 1 if a > b, 0 if a === b, and 1 otherwise.

name: src/native/increasing.js
content:
/**
 * Compare two objects in increasing order using the native comparison and
 * equality operators.
 *
 * @param {Object} a - The first parameter.
 * @param {Object} b - The second parameter.
 * @return {Number} -1 if a < b, 0 if a === b, and 1 otherwise.
 */
export const increasing = ( a , b ) => ( a < b ) ? -1 : ( a === b ) ? 0 : 1 ;

name: increasing
description:
Compare two objects in increasing order using the native comparison and
equality operators.

return.description: 1 if a < b, 0 if a === b, and 1 otherwise.

name: src/proxy/attr/attr.js
content:
/**
 * Generates a binary attribute comparator
 * from a binary comparator and an attribute key.
 *
 * @param {Function} compare - The function used to order attributes.
 * @param {Object} key - The key of the attribute used in the comparison.
 * @return {Function} The function that orders objects by attribute.
 */
export const attr = ( compare , key ) => ( a , b ) => compare( a[key] , b[key] ) ;

name: attr
description:
Generates a binary attribute comparator
from a binary comparator and an attribute key.

params.name: compare
params.description: The function used to order attributes.

params.name: key
params.description: The key of the attribute used in the comparison.

return.description: The function that orders objects by attribute.

name: src/proxy/fn.js
content:
/**
 * Generates a binary comparator
 * from a binary comparator and a function.
 *
 * @param {Function} compare - The function used to order values.
 * @param {Function} callable - The function that generates values used in the comparison.
 * @return {Function} The function that orders objects by value.
 */
export const fn = ( compare , callable ) => ( a , b ) => compare( callable( a ) , callable( b ) ) ;

Generates a binary comparator
from a binary comparator and a function.

params.description: The function used to order values.

params.name: callable

return.description: The function that orders objects by value.

name: src/tools/reverse.js
content:
/**
 * Reverse the order of a comparator.
 *
 * @param {Function} compare - The comparator to reverse.
 * @return {Function} A function f such that compare(a,b) === f(b,a) for all a,b.
 */
export const reverse = compare => ( a , b ) => compare( b , a ) ;

name: reverse
description: Reverse the order of a comparator.

return.description: A function f such that compare(a,b) === f(b,a) for all a,b.

name: src/tools/sign.js
content:
/**
 * Computes the sign of the input number.
 *
 * @param {Number} v - The number to compute the sign of.
 * @return {Number} -1 if v < 0, 1 if v > 0, 0 otherwise.
 */
export const sign = v => v < 0 ? -1 : v > 0 ? 1 : 0 ;

name: sign
description: Computes the sign of the input number.

params.name: v
params.description: The number to compute the sign of.

[@aureooms/js-compare](http://aureooms.github.io/js-compare)
==

Comparison functions for JavaScript.
See [docs](https://aureooms.github.io/js-compare/index.html).

```js
let compare = reverse( lexicographical( increasing ) ) ;
compare( [ 1 , 1 ] , [ 1 , 2 ] )  >  0 ; // true
```

content:
# Installation

Can be managed using
[yarn](https://yarnpkg.com/en/docs),
[npm](https://docs.npmjs.com),
or [jspm](https://jspm.org/docs).


### yarn
```terminal
yarn add @aureooms/js-compare
```

### npm
```terminal
npm install @aureooms/js-compare --save
```

### jspm
```terminal
jspm install npm:@aureooms/js-compare
```
